# =============================================================================
# SPF LEVELS (Security Protection Factor)
# =============================================================================
SPF_LEVELS:
  SPF-15 (Basic Protection):
    - Use Case: Internal tools, dev environments
    - Threats Blocked: Casual attackers, automated scans
    - Features: Basic auth, input validation, logging
    - Overhead: Minimal (< 2ms latency)
    - Cost: Low
    
  SPF-30 (Standard Protection):
    - Use Case: Business applications, customer portals
    - Threats Blocked: Sophisticated individuals, known malware
    - Features: MFA, encryption at rest, IDS/IPS
    - Overhead: Low (< 5ms latency)
    - Cost: Moderate
    
  SPF-50 (High Protection) ← RECOMMENDED:
    - Use Case: Financial services, healthcare, PII handling
    - Threats Blocked: Organized crime, advanced malware, APTs
    - Features: Zero trust, E2E encryption, behavioral analytics
    - Overhead: Moderate (< 10ms latency)
    - Cost: Standard
    
  SPF-100 (Maximum Protection):
    - Use Case: Defense, critical infrastructure, classified
    - Threats Blocked: Nation states, zero-days, quantum attacks
    - Features: Quantum-resistant, air-gapped, formal verification
    - Overhead: High (< 50ms latency)
    - Cost: Premium

# =============================================================================
# WARNINGS & PRECAUTIONS
# =============================================================================
WARNINGS:
  - Apply 15 minutes before exposure (warmup period required)
  - Reapply frequently (security measures degrade over time)
  - Not a substitute for other security measures (defense in depth)
  - Can cause mild irritation (false positives on edge cases)
  - Test on small area first (pilot deployment recommended)
  - Keep out of eyes (don't block monitoring/logging)
  - For external use only (applies to public-facing systems)

PRECAUTIONS:
  - Discontinue if severe irritation occurs (> 5% false positives)
  - Consult security professional for sensitive applications
  - May not protect against all threats (zero-days exist)
  - Effectiveness decreases over time (update regularly)
  - Not waterproof (security degrades under attack)
  - Avoid contact with incompatible systems

# =============================================================================
# CONTRAINDICATIONS
# =============================================================================
CONTRAINDICATIONS:
  - Known allergy to security controls (legacy systems)
  - Extremely sensitive systems (medical implants, life support)
  - Systems requiring zero latency (hard real-time)
  - Incompatible with certain architectures (check compatibility)
  - During active incident response (may interfere with forensics)

# =============================================================================
# ANALOGIES (AGI Construct Mapping)
# =============================================================================
ANALOGY: cognitive_protection.scm

ALEXANDER_PATTERN: "Thick Walls" - Strong protection without isolation
ALEXANDER_PRINCIPLES:
  - Thick Walls: Robust defense mechanisms
  - Filtered Light: Controlled access, not complete blocking
  - Defensible Space: Clear security boundaries
  - Intimacy Gradient: Progressive trust levels
  - Entrance Transition: Graduated security checkpoints

AGI_COMPONENTS:
  - Input Validation: UV filter equivalent
  - Adversarial Defense: Broad-spectrum protection
  - Encryption Layer: Physical/chemical barrier
  - Authentication: Identity verification
  - Monitoring: Immune system equivalent

SUNSCREEN_SCIENCE_PARALLEL:
  UV_Radiation → Cyber_Attacks:
    - UVA (long-wave): Advanced persistent threats
    - UVB (short-wave): Common injection attacks
    - UVC (blocked by atmosphere): Prevented by infrastructure
    
  Protection_Mechanisms:
    - Physical (Zinc/Titanium): Encryption, authentication
    - Chemical (Avobenzone): Active defense, filtering
    - Reapplication: Continuous monitoring, updates
    - Broad-Spectrum: Defense in depth, layered security
    
  SPF_Rating → Security_Level:
    - SPF 15 = blocks 93% → Basic security
    - SPF 30 = blocks 97% → Standard security
    - SPF 50 = blocks 98% → High security
    - SPF 100 = blocks 99% → Maximum security

