# =============================================================================
SYNERGISTIC_COMBINATIONS:
  Morning_Routine:
    1. Cleanser (cognitive-data-prep) - Sanitize inputs
    2. Moisturizer (memory-retention) - Secure context
    3. Sunscreen (THIS PRODUCT) - Protect everything
    
  Evening_Routine:
    1. Cleanser - Review and sanitize logs
    2. Scar Repair (self-healing) - Fix any breaches
    3. Moisturizer - Consolidate security learnings
    
  Problem_Solving:
    1. If breached: Scar Repair first, then reapply sunscreen
    2. If under attack: Increase SPF level immediately
    3. After incident: Full security refresh cycle

# =============================================================================
# PROFESSIONAL RECOMMENDATIONS
# =============================================================================
DERMATOLOGIST_EQUIVALENT (Security Expert Tips):
  - Never skip sunscreen, even indoors (internal threats exist)
  - Higher SPF is better for prolonged exposure (sustained attacks)
  - Physical sunscreens (encryption) are gentler than chemical (filtering)
  - Reapply after swimming (after major system changes)
  - Use year-round, not just in summer (threats are constant)
  - Combine with protective clothing (network segmentation)
  - Check ingredients for skin type (customize for your architecture)

